			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~EditorDavid">EditorDavid</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~EditorDavid">( 4512125 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> <span class="badgeicon"><a href="//slashdot.org/"><img src="//a.fsdn.com/sd/badge_slashdot.png" alt="Works for Slashdot" title="Works for Slashdot"></a></span>
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64696710"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64696710">Tuesday Japan's prime minister Fumio Kishida marked the anniversary of the bombing Tuesday <a href="https://www.voanews.com/a/as-japan-marks-atomic-bomb-anniversaries-military-emerges-from-shadows-of-world-war-ii-/7733340.html" title="voanews.com">at a somber memorial event</a> [voanews.com].<br> <br>

He said "It is the mission of Japan, the only country to have suffered nuclear war, to pass on the reality of the atomic bombings to future generations."</div>
	</div>

